Defendant Julian M Lopez in court with attorney Thomas J Flanagan.  Defendant Julian M Lopez in custody.  Miriam S Falk on behalf of Jennifer Williams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS, concurrent with case 13CF5487, with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  

Defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant IS appropriate for the Substance Abuse Program.

If revoked, court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 4 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction, to be used at the discretion of the agent;
2) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
3) Pay all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) Complete batterers intervention class and AODA assessment. If these are not completed by release, they are to be completed while on probation;
5) Obtain HSED or GED;
6) Obtain further educational or vocational training;
7) Maintain full time schooling and part time employment (16 hours) OR maintain full time employment while taking at least one educational class;
8) No violent contact with the victim;
9) Attend parenting class; Court will allow the parenting class to be completed with the victim present;

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
